# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used in a windows/mac/linux mixed environment,
#   it might be better to exclude it if you suffer from locking issues.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be checked in.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be checked in.
#pdm.lock

